Dialogue: 1,0:08:23.49,0:08:26.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它们太小了所以看上去就像白色一样
Dialogue: 2,0:08:23.49,0:08:26.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They're just so small. They look like white to your eye
Dialogue: 1,0:08:27.71,0:08:31.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,得到白色之前，你能看到红绿蓝变成了黄青品三色
Dialogue: 2,0:08:27.71,0:08:31.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Before you get white red green and blue blurs into yellow cyan and magenta
Dialogue: 1,0:08:31.91,0:08:35.05,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为我把相机挪了挪，让它失焦了
Dialogue: 2,0:08:31.91,0:08:35.05,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And that's what happens here when I move the screen slightly out of focus
Dialogue: 1,0:08:37.82,0:08:42.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,第一次这么近距离看我这系列的慢动作视频，我要吐了
Dialogue: 2,0:08:37.82,0:08:42.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This is too close to watch the Slow Mo Guys video. I might vomit
Dialogue: 1,0:08:43.62,0:08:45.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,CRT情况也一样
Dialogue: 2,0:08:43.62,0:08:45.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,It's the same situation
Dialogue: 1,0:08:46.29,0:08:48.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,只是像素块大点
Dialogue: 2,0:08:46.29,0:08:48.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Just entire blocks and they're bigger
Dialogue: 1,0:08:50.45,0:08:57.34,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我之前提过，典型LCD显示器是用CCFL点亮的
Dialogue: 2,0:08:50.45,0:08:57.34,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As I mentioned before this is a 4k LCD screen which a while back were typically lit by CCFLs or
Dialogue: 1,0:08:57.63,0:09:04.42,1080CN,,0,0,0,,全称叫冷阴极荧光灯管，也就是说整个屏幕是被荧光灯点亮的
Dialogue: 2,0:08:57.63,0:09:04.42,1080EN,,0,0,0,,A cold cathode fluorescent lamp which means the entire panel is backlit by fluorescent tubes
Dialogue: 1,0:09:05.04,0:09:06.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而现在呢
Dialogue: 2,0:09:05.04,0:09:06.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Nowadays
Dialogue: 1,0:09:06.48,0:09:08.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它们是用LED灯点亮的
Dialogue: 2,0:09:06.48,0:09:08.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They are backlit by LEDs
Dialogue: 1,0:09:08.54,0:09:15.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以才叫“LED电视”。而LED比LCD的好处在于
Dialogue: 2,0:09:08.54,0:09:15.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This is why this would actually be marketed as an LED TV. The benefit of LED screens over CCFL screens
Dialogue: 1,0:09:15.44,0:09:16.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它们更薄
Dialogue: 2,0:09:15.44,0:09:16.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,is that they're a lot thinner
Dialogue: 1,0:09:16.87,0:09:23.22,1080CN,,0,0,0,,现在我要把相机挪到黑色的部分。有趣的是尽管该区域是黑色的
Dialogue: 2,0:09:16.87,0:09:23.22,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Now I'm going to point it at where some black text is. Now interestingly even though this area is black
Dialogue: 1,0:09:23.22,0:09:28.99,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为所有的子像素都暗下去了，它们仍然是有背景光的，一会给你们看
Dialogue: 2,0:09:23.22,0:09:28.99,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Because all the sub pixels are dimmed. They are still in fact backlit. Let me show you that right now
Dialogue: 1,0:09:29.81,0:09:32.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当我们挪到这时，抱歉因为曝光度问题画面噪声有点高
Dialogue: 2,0:09:29.81,0:09:32.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,now you can see as we push in here you have to pardon noise
Dialogue: 1,0:09:32.85,0:09:36.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当我们挪到这时，抱歉因为曝光度问题画面噪声有点高
Dialogue: 2,0:09:32.85,0:09:36.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,for an extremely high ISO to get this shot through a macro lens
Dialogue: 1,0:09:36.25,0:09:38.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你能看见液晶显示器上的暗的像素点
Dialogue: 2,0:09:36.25,0:09:38.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,You can see even the dimmed pixels part of the liquid crystal
Dialogue: 1,0:09:38.98,0:09:42.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在尽量挡住后面的光穿过
Dialogue: 2,0:09:38.98,0:09:42.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,display as it's now trying to block all light from penetrating through
Dialogue: 1,0:09:42.65,0:09:46.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但它肯定不能完全挡住，总会有点亮，所以这就是
Dialogue: 2,0:09:42.65,0:09:46.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but it's still a backlit pixel, and that's one of the fundamental
Dialogue: 1,0:09:46.13,0:09:49.57,1080CN,,0,0,0,,LCD显示器的缺点之一。你能在LCD显示器上
Dialogue: 2,0:09:46.13,0:09:49.57,1080EN,,0,0,0,,limitations of an LCD screen. You can see this effect on an LCD screen
Dialogue: 1,0:09:49.64,0:09:53.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,看到这一点，当你看一幅几乎全黑的图的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:09:49.64,0:09:53.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,in the credits of a film because got almost completely black image
Dialogue: 1,0:09:53.20,0:09:55.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为上面还有白色的字
Dialogue: 2,0:09:53.20,0:09:55.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But because there's white text the entire
Dialogue: 1,0:09:55.35,0:10:00.19,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以就必须有背光，导致总有光会从黑色像素点漏出来
Dialogue: 2,0:09:55.35,0:10:00.19,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Backlight has to be on to display the white which means light will leak out from the black pixels
Dialogue: 1,0:10:00.20,0:10:02.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也就是说这不是真的黑色
Dialogue: 2,0:10:00.20,0:10:02.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Which means it's not true black
Dialogue: 1,0:10:02.52,0:10:07.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最近一项新技术也越来越流行了，叫作OLED屏幕
Dialogue: 2,0:10:02.52,0:10:07.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,There is another technology that's becoming much more common these days and that is an OLED-screen
Dialogue: 1,0:10:07.35,0:10:12.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,全称有机发光二极管。我的确想做LCD和OLED屏幕的对比
Dialogue: 2,0:10:07.35,0:10:12.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Organic light-emitting diode. I did want to include a comparison between an LCD panel and an OLED panel
Dialogue: 1,0:10:12.98,0:10:18.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但我没有OLED电视，不过还好在我录制这期视频过程当中
Dialogue: 2,0:10:12.98,0:10:18.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But I didn't actually have an OLED TV and by sheer luck right in the middle of me shooting all this footage
Dialogue: 1,0:10:19.07,0:10:24.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,LG联系到了我，给我提供了一款OLED电视来做测评
Dialogue: 2,0:10:19.07,0:10:24.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,LG got in touch and offered to supply me with an OLED TV for the purpose of making this video
Dialogue: 1,0:10:24.15,0:10:27.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,非常感谢LG。所以一起来看看吧！
Dialogue: 2,0:10:24.15,0:10:27.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which I really appreciate, thanks, LG. What are we going to take a look at it?
Dialogue: 1,0:10:28.05,0:10:34.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这是LG的77寸OLED电视。OLED的工作原理是每个像素点
Dialogue: 2,0:10:28.05,0:10:34.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This is a 77 inch LG OLED TV. The way OLED technology works is that each pixel is
Dialogue: 1,0:10:34.74,0:10:38.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,会根据电压来自身发光
Dialogue: 2,0:10:34.74,0:10:38.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Self-illuminating depending on how much voltage is passing through it
Dialogue: 1,0:10:38.27,0:10:41.37,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以电视本身不需要全局的背光
Dialogue: 2,0:10:38.27,0:10:41.37,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which means there's no global backlight on the TV
Dialogue: 1,0:10:41.37,0:10:44.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每个像素点亮度单独受控
Dialogue: 2,0:10:41.37,0:10:44.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Each pixel is individually in control of
Dialogue: 1,0:10:44.47,0:10:49.69,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而不是靠背光，使得我们在用高感光度
Dialogue: 2,0:10:44.47,0:10:49.69,1080EN,,0,0,0,,how bright it is and it's not being lit from behind and that means when we go to our high ISO
Dialogue: 1,0:10:50.27,0:10:54.46,1080CN,,0,0,0,,实验时——就像对LCD做的一样——当屏幕出现一块黑色的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:10:50.27,0:10:54.46,1080EN,,0,0,0,,experiment just like we've done the LCD that when there's an area of black on the screen
Dialogue: 1,0:10:54.56,0:10:56.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所有像素点都是关闭的
Dialogue: 2,0:10:54.56,0:10:56.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,All of those pixels are off
Dialogue: 1,0:10:56.77,0:11:03.04,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你能看到当我把光标挪过来时，这些子像素点又亮起来
Dialogue: 2,0:10:56.77,0:11:03.04,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And you can see here where I'm putting my cursor in front of the lens you can see each sub pixel lighting up and then
Dialogue: 1,0:11:03.12,0:11:04.97,1080CN,,0,0,0,,光标挪走时又全灭
Dialogue: 2,0:11:03.12,0:11:04.97,1080EN,,0,0,0,,completely turning off when it goes away
Dialogue: 1,0:11:04.97,0:11:11.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这项技术使得显示更暗的黑色、与更薄的屏幕成为可能
Dialogue: 2,0:11:04.97,0:11:11.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This technology means much deeper blacks and the possibility of a very thin screen
Dialogue: 1,0:11:11.33,0:11:15.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以就这样啦，电视在慢动作下的工作原理
Dialogue: 2,0:11:11.33,0:11:15.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And there you have it a brief explanation of how a TV works in slow-mo
